Description:
STANDS OUT LIKE A CANDLE IN THE WIND
"House hunting is like a game of Where's Wally - you know what you're looking for but it's hard to find. Well, now you've finally found your Waldo. Welcome to 2 Topaz Way."
The heart-warming, inviting home will inspire a generation. With stunning features and an unbridled integrity the property is the perfect fit for a queen and her family.
The home is the unique blend of joyous family living and strong, independent characteristics that were ahead of its time.
For example:
- At the heart of the home is the open plan living/dining room adjacent to the kitchen where the family can gather together;
- But at either end of the home are independent living quarters for a kids' rumpus room and a parents retreat;
- The decked area is central to the home and is conveniently west-facing to make the most of the setting sun;
- But on the south side is a courtyard which is perfect for a basketball area or a child's play area.
Located in the heart of Officer, it's walking distance to the train station, shops, Bridgewood Primary and Officer Secondary schools.
Other features include:
- A master bedroom with a walk-in robe and en-suite;
- Remaining bedrooms with walk-in robes;
- The house is fitted with heating and cooling;
- And includes a double car garage with remote access and dual entry points.
Be at peace, you're finally home.
Ray White prides itself on being as accurate as possible however anyone considering purchasing the property should undertake their own due diligence to confirm the above.
